OL,3,EHAUNTED CHRISTMAS HOUSEG`````Ww3/7/c{  
OL,4,BI'm intending to spend the   W||<||~  
OL,5,BChristmas period in a hauntedW*s~%> 
OL,6,Bhouse once owned by EbeneezerWh8((z}  
OL,7,BScrooge. At least, that's    W*?  
OL,8,Bwhat the landlord says. But   Wo%  
OL,9,Bthen, the landlord is also a  W"o'  B
OL,10,Bconvicted clock thief.                 
OL,12,FMy bedroom is cosy enough, though I'm  
OL,13,Fnot sure about the blood that pours    
OL,14,Fdown the walls at midnight, and I'm not
OL,15,Ftoo keen on the way the bed keeps being
OL,16,Fraised off the floor and exploding.    
OL,17,FWhen it happened last night one of the 
OL,18,Fmattress springs speared my nightshirt.
